                <h1>How Long Does a 5150 Stay on Your Record in California?</h1>
                <p>In California, a 5150 hold, which is a temporary psychiatric hold for individuals deemed a danger to themselves or others, generally does not appear on a public criminal record. However, it may be noted in mental health records. The duration it stays in these records can vary but is typically not permanent. Consulting a legal expert for detailed guidance is recommended.</p>
